ractured politics, the fruits of growth may rot before everyone has a chance to enjoy them. It’s high time to ask where progress is taking us, and are we nearly there yet? In fact, Trebeck and Williams claim in this ground-breaking book, the challenge is now to make ourselves at home with this wealth, to ensure, in the interests of equality, that everyone is included. They explore the possibility of ‘Arrival’, urging us to move from enlarging the economy to improving it, and the benefits this would bring for all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEconomic development. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh1 aRaworth, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Jeremy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z9783111196688oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144733726340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447337843?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447337843423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447337843/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2019